<HEADLINE> Palestinian Faction Condemns Hebron killing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The Hebron Regional Committee
of Fatah Wednesday condemned the Tuesday shooting incident against
the Palestinian workers in Hebron and called on all Palestinians
to fight against Israeli military occupation.
</P>
<P>
In an announcement, Fatah, the main stream of the Palestinian
Liberation Organization, set Wednesday as the mourning day for the
three Palestinians killed by Israeli soliders Tuesday night near
the West Bank city of Hebron.
</P>
<P>
It also set Thursday as a day of activities and clashes with
Jewish settlers and Israeli soldiers across the occupied
territories, and Saturday a day for a huge march by Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Israeli soldiers opened fire at a van filled with Palestinian
workers at Tarkumia checkpoint near Hebron, killing three of
them. The fatalities were identified as Ghaleb Rajoub, a relative
of West Bank Preventive Security Chief Jibril Rajoub, Mohammed
Sharowna and Adnan Abu Zneid.
</P>
<P>
Israeli authorities on Wednesday admitted that the Israeli
soldiers should be responsible for the killing. Commander of the
Central Region of the Israel Defense Force (IDF) Uzi Dayan said
that interrogations have shown that the driver of the van was not
intended to hit one of the Israeli soldiers, but the car was on
high speed when crossing the checkpoint.
</P>
<P>
The killing incident has caused sharp criticism from all walks
of life of the Palestinians. Palestinian National Authority (PNA)
President Yasser Arafat called it "a big crime against
Palestinian workers."
</P>
<P>
Israeli President Ezer Weizman and Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu phoned Arafat on Wednesday to express condolence for
those killed.
</P>
<P>
The killing incident also caused widespread protests in Hebron
and another West Bank city Ramallah on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In Hebron, local residents clashed with Israeli forces in
various parts of the city and its nearby areas and at least 50
Palestinians were injured by rubber bullets and tear gas fired by
the Israeli forces, witnesses told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
In Ramallah, students from the Birzeit University took to the
streets and clashed with the Israeli troops near Balou on
Ramallah-Nablus main road, and at least seven students were hurt
by rubber bullets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
