<HEADLINE> TAZARA Provides Zambia with Most Competitive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania-Zambia-Railway (TAZARA)
provides Zambia with the most competitive route to the sea,
TAZARA managing director Kingston Mkandawire has said.
</P>
<P>
Zambian News Agency Wednesday quoted Mkandawire as saying here
that TAZARA has reduced the number of days to three from the
previous 11 for freight goods from Kapiri Mposhi, the end of the
China-built railway in Zambia, to Dar es Salaam seaport of
Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The current cost and efficiency, he said, give the
1,860-kilometre railway a new lease of life to meet the challenge
in the freight business because it has learned from its past
performance.
</P>
<P>
TAZARA will do the best it can in terms of good business
partnership, he said.
</P>
<P>
From July this year all TAZARA employees will be paid in U.S.
Dollars equivalent in order to redress salary differences between
Zambians and Tanzanians, according to the director.
</P>
<P>
Salim Musona, Tanzanian Permanent Secretary of the Ministry of
Communication and Transport, has assured Zambia that the problem
of pilferage has been brought under control on TAZARA and Dar es
Salaam port.
</P>
<P>
The visiting Tanzanian official said his country has
reinforced security by increasing personnel to man the harbor as
well as control the movement of cargo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
