<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-11 17:14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus to Issue Special Coin for WWF </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The Central Bank of Cyprus
announced Wednesday that a special coin will be issued to
commemorate the work of the World Wild Fund for Nature (WWF).
</P>
<P>
The limited-edition coin depicts a Green Turtle (Chelonia
Mydas) and will be available from March 23. The coinage was done
at the British mint in England.
</P>
<P>
Three thousand silver coins in presentation boxes will be
available for 12.50 Cyprus pounds (about 25 U.S. dollars) each,
while another 3,000 copper coins will be available for one pound
and eight cents (about 2.16 U.S. dollars) each.
</P>
<P>
The Green Turtle nests its eggs in the Akamas peninsula, at the
westmost part of Cyprus, near the Lara and Toxeftra bay.
</P>
<P>
The International Union for the Conservation of Nature (IUCN)
lists the Green Turtle as an endangered species.
</P>
<P>
According to the IUCN, the annual number of Green Turtle
nesting females in the entire Mediterranean could be as low as
325 to 375.
</P>
<P>
Apart from Cyprus, they nest in very few other known
locations. They depend on the beaches of Akamas for their
survival in the Mediterranean.
</P>
<P>
International and local environmental groups have launched a
series of campaigns, demanding the protection of the area and its
declaration into a National Park, thus providing full protection
for the nesting sites. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980312.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwandan Govt Cancels over 1,000 High School </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 11 (Xinhua)- The Rwandan Ministry of Education
has cancelled over 1,000 high school certificates following the
discovery of a series of fraud and irregularities in some
schools.
</P>
<P>
"The Ministry did not dump any certificate," Jean Pierre
Bizimana, Minister of State, told reporters Tuesday night,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
It is alleged that some schools failed to abide by the rules
established by the Ministry of Education relating to
deliberations and therefore, accorded certificates to students
who have failed in four or more subjects.
</P>
<P>
This measure also hits those who skipped some years of high
school, or moved to other schools without an official transfer.
</P>
<P>
Most seriously hit are about 400 graduates from Butamwa
Polytechnic School.
</P>
<P>
According to the Minister of State, all the 400 certificates
must be cancelled because the school did not abide by the
Ministry's curricula.
</P>
<P>
This new crisis in offering certificates adds to intricacies
that have characterized the Ministry of Education after the 1994
genocide.
</P>
<P>
It was quite a challenge to harmonize the schooling system in
a country which had then turned into a melting-pot for returnees
from English-speaking east African countries and others from
Francophone countries like Burundi, and former Zaire.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Bizimana told the press that the Rwanda
National University cannot open its doors for 1998-1999 academic
year due to a serious lack of lecturers.
</P>
<P>
Initially planned for March 1, 1998, the opening ceremonies
have been postponed to April. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
