<HEADLINE> West Countries Criticized for Imposing West </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi
Wednesday criticized western countries and donor agencies to
force African nations to accept their economic and political
systems.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the African diplomatic corps who paid a courtesy
call to the president here, Moi noted that these systems were
incompatible with individual needs of African countries.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan leader decried that Africa had for a long time been
used for political experiment, most of which had gone wrong.
</P>
<P>
Economic and political systems grown up in Africa are going
away because African nations have been arm-twisted into accepting
irrelevant systems, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
