individual problems and needs in an honest manner without trying
to please anyone, adding that African problems would have to be
solved by Africans themselves.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, the Dean of the African diplomatic corps,
Clarkson Umelo who is the Nigerian High Commissioner to Kenya,
saluted President Moi for his unrelenting crusade for peace in
East, Central and the Horn of Africa.
</P>
<P>
He told the president that it was on the account of this and
other initiatives that other African heads of state hold him in
high esteem as a prominent peace broker and elder statesman.
