that the Congress does not support what our troops are doing in
Bosnia," chairman Benjamin Gilman, Republican of New York, said.
</P>
<P>
In December last year, U.S. President Bill Clinton decided to
maintain an open-ended military presence in Bosnia after twice
missing deadlines for a U.S. withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
At present, the United States has 8,500 troops in Bosnia, and
the number could be reduced to 6,900. 
