<HEADLINE> Better Protection for Lawmakers Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- A senior Party official today
called for better protection of the legitimate rights and
interests of deputies to people's congresses at all levels,
China's legislative bodies.
</P>
<P>
At a full meeting of deputies from south China's Guangdong
Province to the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), China's
top legislature, in session here since last Thursday, Deputy Li
Changchun said that deputies to people's congresses at all levels
are serving as a powerful supervisory force.
</P>
<P>
"Standing committees of people's congresses at all levels
should take effective measures to protect the deputies' legitimate
rights and interests, to enable them to perform their duties
boldly," said Li, a member of the Political Bureau of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and also
newly-appointed secretary of the Guangdong Provincial Committee of
the CPC.
</P>
<P>
He said that there are 150,000 deputies to the people's
congresses at all levels in Guangdong alone, who can play the role
of "a bridge" between the Party and government departments and the
general public.
</P>
<P>
"We should open channels for these deputies so as to directly
put forth complaints or suggestions to principal leading officials
of local Party committees and to guarantee that they get a prompt
and satisfactory answer," he urged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
