<HEADLINE> Russia Draws Up Employment Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Russian government Thursday
approved a federal employment program to run from 1998 to 2000 to
cut unemployment.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax news agency quoted Minister for Labor and Social
Development Marina Moskvina as saying the program is expected to
keep unemployment at 3.6 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
The program envisions consulting services for about 25 million
people on potential jobs and benefit payments to about 10 million
unemployed.
</P>
<P>
Reports said the program will be financed from the State
Employment Fund and from the federal budget. In 1998, the State
Employment Fund is to allocate about one billion Russian rubles
(160 million U.S. dollars) to this program. 
</P>
