<HEADLINE> Tianjin to Emerge as North China's Leading Economic Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin Municipality is striving
to turn itself into a modern port city and a leading economic
center in north China in line with directives of the central
government.
</P>
<P>
Compared with other metropolises in China, Tianjin has a host
of advantages, said Zhang Lichang, secretary of Tianjin Municipal
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), at a panel
discussion of the Ninth National People's Congress in session here
since last week.
</P>
<P>
Among others, Tianjin is one of the best ports in north China.
Located in the center of the Bohai Rim area, the city is connected
with the New Euro-Asian Continental Bridge, he said.
</P>
<P>
To attain its goal, he added, Tianjin Municipality will strive
to boost its commerce and trade, harbor construction, information
technology, finance and high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Tianjin economic and technological zone, the bonded
zone and new harbor area will serve as the backbone of its
economic growth. And the municipality will be turned into a hub
for interflows of capital, information, technological and talents.
</P>
