<HEADLINE> Stability Returns to Xinjiang After Crackdown on Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The crackdown on terrorist
activities in northwest Xinjian autonomous region has resulted in
an improved public security situation there, according to a senior
official of the Xinjiang regional government.
</P>
<P>
"The move has been successful...Xinjiang is enjoying political
and social stability, and people are living happily and with
contentment," said Wang Lequan, secretary of Xinjiang Regional
Committee of the Communist Party of China at a press conference
hosted here today by the ongoing session of the Ninth National
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
According to Wang, the crackdown was launched in the region
after the eruption early last year of a series of violent
terrorist activities including robbery, killing with guns and
bus-bombing.
</P>
<P>
Such terrorist activities were perpetuated by a handful of bad
people who want to split China, sow dissension among various
ethnic groups and sabotage relations between the government and
people, Wang noted.
</P>
<P>
One of the measures taken by the regional government is to
educate people in patriotism while exposing the true nature of the
separatists, said Wang. "We also encourage people to expose bad
people and criminal activities," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Now most cases of terrorism have been cracked, with
criminals arrested and given due punishment according to law,"
Wang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
