<HEADLINE> Andres Scores Twice, Beijing Takes Chinese Super Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WENZHOU, Zhejiang, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Andres' second
goal in last two minutes of the "Sudden Death" play to avenge the
Beijing Guo'an's last year defeat to the Dalian Wanda, winning the
1997 Chinese soccer Super Cup Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
Andres, who was top foreigner in scoring and ranked second in
all with 10 goals last season, hit his first goal in the 88th
mintue to force the match into an extra time.
</P>
<P>
"Dalian was better team but they didn't play well tonight. we
tried our best and won the Cup," Beijing coach Shen Xiangfu said.
</P>
<P>
Wang Tao put the Wandan on a 1-0 lead when he scored a pass
from teammate Wei Yiming near the goalmouth 16 minutes into the
first half.
</P>
<P>
Three players, including two of the Guo'an's, were called out
of the pitch after they drew three red cards.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Super Cup was played between the Chinese league
champion and China's Cup titlist every year.
</P>
<P>
Dalian edged Beijing 3-2 to take the Cup last year. 
