<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Session Holds Third Speech Meeting (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The ongoing First Session of the
Ninth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), China's top advisory body, held
its third and last speech meeting this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, a total of 31 members of the Ninth CPPCC National
Committee have had a chance to speak out their suggestions for the
central government on running state affairs at full meetings of
the current CPPCC session.
</P>
<P>
Luo Gan, a member of the Political Bureau and the Secretariat
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, and Qian
Qichen, vice premier and also a member of the CPC Central
Committee's Political Bureau, attended today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the secretariat of the current session show
that nearly 50 Party and state leaders and heads of ministries and
commissions under the State Council attended the three speech
meetings to hear advices from the CPPCC members.
</P>
<P>
A major topic for today's speakers is promoting China's
peaceful reunification with the principle of "one country, two
systems".
</P>
<P>
In a speech on behalf of the Central Committee of the
Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang (RCCK), Member
Zhou Tienong, who is vice-chairman of the RCCK Central Committee,
urged people of insight within the Taiwan Kuomintang to comply
with the wishes of Taiwan people, return to the stance of "one
China", and take concrete steps to promote an early realization of
political negotiations across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Member Zeng Chonglang, who is vice president of the All-China
Federation of Taiwan Compatriots, said that "one country, two
systems" is the best way to maintain the existing social,
political systems and way of life in Taiwan and protect the
long-term interests of the Taiwan compatriots.
</P>
</TEXT>
