<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy, Albania to Sign Customs Assistance Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Italy and Albania are to sign a
customs assistance agreement as part of a European Union
assistance program to Albania, the European Commission said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Mario Monti, Italian commissioner for customs affairs, signed a
declaration Thursday in Tirana, Albania, marking the conclusion of
the agreement between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Italy would provide two patrol vessels to
assist Albania's customs administration in its monitoring and
supervision of commercial maritime traffic and in the prevention
of smuggling.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the executive body of the 15-nation
union, will grant the accord 225,000 ECUs (240,750 dollars) under
the framework of its memorandum of understanding on the customs
assistance to Albania, which was signed last November.
</P>
<P>
A European customs assistance mission was set up in Tirana last
June. It was part of the commission's response to a request for
support from the Albanian government to the international
community following unrest in the country in early 1997.
</P>
<P>
The mission will continue until the end of this year to assist
the Albanian customs authorities in ensuring the collection of
customs duties and in intercepting smuggling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980312.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen on International Situation and Diplomatic Work (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Noting that he once visited the Middle East region, and has
been to Egypt, Israel, Syria, and Palestine, Qian said he went
there only for the purpose of acquainting himself with the
situation there and setting forth some of China's views on the
Middle East issue.
</P>
<P>
China will not be a mediator or go-between on the Middle East
question, he said, adding that the settlement of middle-east issue
should be listed on the agenda after the Iraqi Weapon Inspection
crisis is initially settled, so as to continue advancing the
middle-east peaceful process.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that all parties concerned are able to continue
advancing the peaceful process, the Chinese vice-premier said.
</P>
<P>
In response to questions on Hong Kong, Qian said he has every
confidence in the up-coming election of the Legislative Council in
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) in May, which
will surely be just, fair and open.
</P>
<P>
He said the coming May will see the election for the first
legislative council in Hong Kong. The methods, the work of
organizing and all essential preparations are all devised,
organized and conducted by the Hong Kong SAR government, and the
central government does not plan to send any people there to
monitor the election.
</P>
<P>
The deputies to the NPC and members of the CPPCC National
Committee from the HKSAR have come to Beijing, which demonstrates
that the representatives from the HKSAR are also in the position
to participate in the discussions and administration of the state
affairs of the whole of China, he noted, adding they have not come
to Beijing for the purpose of discussing affairs concerning the
Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
With regard to individual remarks, everybody has his freedom
for what he likes to say, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
Turning to Macao issue, he said the Preparatory Committee of
the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) will be established
very soon.
</P>
<P>
"The date of Macao's return to the motherland is drawing
increasingly nearer, and all kinds of related preparatory work is
proceeding smoothly. The Preparatory Committee of the Macao SAR
will be established, and this is a matter that falls within the
scope of the authority of the NPC, he said.
</P>
