<DOCNO> XIE19980312.0072 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen on International Situation and Diplomatic Work (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government intends to
sign the International Covenant on Civil And Political Rights,
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen said here this
morning.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remark at a press conference sponsored by the
ongoing First Session of the Ninth National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has always attached great importance to
international covenants on human rights and has so far signed 17
such conventions, Qian said, noting that China signed the
International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights
last October.
</P>
<P>
In response to a reporter's question concerning China's role in
pursuing a peaceful settlement of the recent Iraqi weapons
inspection crisis, he said, China has played a due, unique and
positive role in the peaceful settlement of the UN weapons
inspection crisis in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
On this issue, he said, "China does not act as a mediator nor
does it put forward any scheme for the settlement," he said.
</P>
<P>
"It adheres to two principles: one is that the relevant UN
Security Council resolutions on the issue must be implemented
earnestly and comprehensively; the other is that China does not
favor the use of force," he said.
</P>
<P>
Qian acknowledged that China has persistently made these two
points clear on various occasions, including multilateral
debates, bilateral consultations, exchange of letters among
leaders, telephone conversations and mutual transmission of
information.
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, China focused its attention on making the five
permanent members of the UN Security Council unanimously agree and
support Kofi Annan, UN secretary-general, in going to Iraq for
negotiations, which was eventually successful.
</P>
<P>
"In this regard, China has played a positive role," Qian said.
</P>
<P>
On the Middles East issue, he stressed, it is beyond any doubt
that China is prepared to play certain roles in promoting the
peaceful process in the Middle East, but that it is not a party to
be directly involved in the Middle East question, or a direct
party to help resolve the Palestine-Israeli dispute.
</P>
</TEXT>
