<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen on International Situation and Diplomatic Work (7) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The European Union is already prepared to impose an arms
embargo on this region, and the United Nations has not yet
discussed it.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that maybe the United Nations is not an appropriate
place for the discussion of this matter, because you can imagine
if arms embargo is only imposed on Yugoslavia, which may not be
able to resolve this matter totally," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We must consider a more appropriate way, and at least this
matter should be resolved through peaceful means, not through
bloodshed," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo question is fundamentally within Yugoslavia,
therefore it is an internal matter of Yugoslavia, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Kosovo is a part of Yugoslavia's territory, and the
Yugoslavian and Serbian governments have the responsibility and
they should be able to handle and deal with this matter
appropriately," he said.
</P>
<P>
Citing the Balkan region a place with very complex relations
among the various ethnic groups in the region, Qian said the
legitimate rights and interests of all the ethnic groups should be
protected.
</P>
<P>
However, the foreign minister called for efforts to be made to
prevent and guard against splittist activities conducted by some
extremists.
</P>
<P>
"If no caution is paid in this regard, then it may give
rise to extensive regional turmoils or even conflicts," Qian
warned.
</P>
<P>
Any measure to be taken by the international community in
dealing with this situation, he said, should be both conducive to
regional peace and stability and refraining from interfering in
the internal affairs of the countries concerned.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that international community should take measures
to safeguard the peace and stability in the region while guarding
against the interference in the internal affairs of the countries
in the region, Qian Qichen said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
