<HEADLINE> Coffee Entreprenurs in E. Africa to Be Organized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Local coffee entreprenurs in
eastern African countries are forming their own organization,
"The Monitor" reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Frederic Kuwuma, executive director of Uganda Coffee Trade
Federation (UCFT), said the proposed Eastern Africa Coffee
Cooperation Forum (EACCF) is aimed at sharing scientific
information between the member states on issues including
scientific research, new technology, training and advocacy.
</P>
<P>
"The forum we are establishing will aim at consolidating our
joint relationships, professional research exchange programs,
advocacy and address coffee production problems at the grassroots
levels," he said.
</P>
<P>
EACCF's membership is to cover Kenya, Tanzania, Ethiopia,
Rwanda, Burundi and Uganda, the executive director said.
</P>
<P>
UCFT has more than 70 members including coffee exporters,
growers, processors, agents, brokers, traders, roasters, insurers
and bankers.
</P>
<P>
It has established wide range of links with international
coffee organizations including the Speciality Coffee Association
of America (SCAA) and the Coffee Trade Federation (CFT) of the
United Kingdom and European Coffee Federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
