<HEADLINE> New Commander of Iran's Mobilization Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Supreme Leader Ayatollah
Ali Khamenei appointed Mohammad Husseinzadeh Hejazi as commander
of the Basij (Mobilization) Resistance Forces on Thursday, the
Iranian official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei, also Commander-in-Chief of the Iranian Armed Forces,
made the decision according to a proposal of the commander of the
Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps (IRGC) Yahya Rahim-Safavi and
"by taking into account Hejazi's valuable records and experiences
during his service at the IRGC and Basij forces," the IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
In his decree, Khamenei expressed the hope that Hejazi would
make use of the potential to form a 20-million-strong Basij force,
organize an active and skilled force and promulgate Basij culture
based on the faith and sacrifices of its members.
</P>
<P>
He also lauded the services of the previous commander of the
Basij forces Alireza Afshar during his term of office.
</P>
<P>
The Basij forces, a military reserve in charge of Iran's
internal security under the command of the IRGC, were formed in
the early 1980s during the 1980-88 Iran-Iraq war according to an
order of the late Iranian Supreme Leader Ayatollah Khomeini.
</P>
</TEXT>
