<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greece's Industrial Production Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Greece's industrial production
jumped by 0.9 percent in 1997 over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Overall mining, industrial and electricity production increased
by 1.3 percent against 1996, figures released by the Greek
National Statistics Service (ESYE) showed Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Industrial production last December alone increased by 7.8
percent and overall production by 5.2 percent against the same
month in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Construction activity from January to December last year rose
by 5.7 percent against the corresponding period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The retail price index in January increased by 0.5 percent
compared with a 0.7 percent rise in the same period last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
