<HEADLINE> Eastern Chinese City Spared In Recent Peak Flooding Period </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The peak of the flood season has
passed in the city of Nanchang, capital of east China's Jiangxi
Province, at 10:00 Wednesday evening without causing any visible
damages to its dikes and bridges.
</P>
<P>
The water's highest point was 23.9 m., almost a meter above the
danger line, but it posed no threat to the city, according to the
latest reports from the provincial flood and drought headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The high water has come as a result of continued rains for the
past few days, causing damage in 18 cities and counties, and a few
casualties, although statistics are still not available. Large
tracts of farmland has also been damaged by the flooding.
</P>
<P>
Local government has sent thousands of people for rescue
operations, according to the provincial headquarters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
