<HEADLINE> NPC Deputies Expect Better Public Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Deputies to the Ninth National
People's Congress expressed the hope that the government and law
enforcement departments would make greater efforts to improve
public security.
</P>
<P>
Surveys conducted by the State Planning Commission and the
Beijing-based Horizon Market Survey and Analysis Company show that
public security ranked lower last year in the list of popular
concerns in the country.
</P>
<P>
The NPC deputies attributed the markdown to severe crackdowns
on criminal offenses over the past two years.
</P>
<P>
"I feel that the public security situation has stabilized on
the whole and that the social order is good," said Zhang Liangji,
director of the Beijing Public Security Bureau. "The government
has made marked achievement in this regard."
</P>
<P>
However, Premier Li Peng noted in his Government Work Report
that people are not satisfied with the public security situation.
And a report of the Ministry of Public Security says that, despite
a decreasing number of crimes in many places, public security
problems have remained serious.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Liangji said that increases in the number of migrant
workers and in the number of laid-off workers have brought
pressures on public security work. He maintained that public
security departments alone cannot solve all problems.
</P>
<P>
"Correct guidance and increased job opportunities for people
can play a good role," he said.
</P>
<P>
Public security remains a heated topic among the NPC deputies.
NPC deputy Li Wenhai said that good public security will provide a
favorable environment for economic growth and win trust from
people for the government.
</P>
<P>
People have a strong hope that the government would strengthen
the armed police and public security departments so as to crack
down on arrogant criminal offenders, said NPC deputy Chen Xianzhi,
an armed policeman from Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
NPC deputy Jia Qinglin, mayor of Beijing, said that the capital
will continue to crack down on criminal offenses this year.
</P>
<P>
NPC deputy Meng Zhiyuan said that all people should be educated
so that they will become better law-abiding citizens.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
