<HEADLINE> Bomb Blasts Damage Car Showrooms in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Two bombs exploded early Thursday
morning in the Greek capital, Athens, causing extensive damage to
two car showrooms in the suburbs of Ellinorosson and Holargos,
police said.
</P>
<P>
The first bomb went off at 12:05 a.m. at a Chrysler car
showroom on Katechaki avenue and the second bomb exploded at an
Opel car showroom on Messoghion avenue.
</P>
<P>
The two devices were similar to those that exploded last month
at two McDonald's fast-food restaurants in the Athens suburbs of
Halandri and Vrilissia, and at a General Motors car showroom on
Kifissias avenue.
</P>
<P>
No one has so far claimed responsibility for Thursday's
explosions, but police believe that the two bombs were planted by
the Greek terrorist group, "November 17." 
</P>
</TEXT>
