<HEADLINE> UNGA President Arrives for Official Visit to Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 12 (Xinhua) -- United Nations General
Assembly (UNGA) President Hennadiy Udovenko arrived here Thursday
night for a three-day official visit to Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko, the Ukrainian Foreign Minister, who succeeded
Malaysia's Razali Ismail as the UNGA president, will call on
Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi at the Foreign Ministry
before having a delegation-level meeting Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko is also scheduled to call on Malaysia's Deputy Prime
Minister Anwar Ibrahim at the Prime Minister's office Friday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He is scheduled to call on Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad on Saturday besides meeting members of the National
Chamber of Commerce and Industry (NCCI) and attending a lunch to
be hosted by the Governing Council of the United Nations
Association of Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The UNGA president will exchange views with the Malaysian
leaders on various issues of interest to Malaysia and Ukraine at
the UN, a foreign ministry statement said.
</P>
<P>
Prior to being assigned as Ukraine foreign minister in
September 1994, Udovenko was Ukraine's ambassador to Poland from
1992 to 1994.
</P>
<P>
Udovenko will leave for Tokyo Saturday night. 
