<HEADLINE> EU Grants Aid to Myanmar Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission on
Thursday granted humanitarian aid worth 1.39 million ECUs (1.48
million U.S. dollars) for Myanmar refugees in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The aid, to be managed by the European Community Humanitarian
Office (ECHO), will enable United Nations institutions and
non-governmental organizations to carry out aid programs in the
next six months.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is offering asylum to nearly 115,000 Myanmar refugees
from ethnic minorities, who are living in camps along the
Myanmar-Thailand border.
</P>
<P>
ECHO is responsible for managing EU humanitarian aid to all
non-European Union countries. In 1997 alone, ECHO made available
aid worth 442 million ECUs (470 million U.S. dollars) in 66
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
