<HEADLINE> All European Conference Opens in London </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The first European conference
between the state leaders from the 15 European Union (EU)
countries and their counterparts from EU applicant central and
eastern European countries opened in London Thursday.
</P>
<P>
British Prime Minister Tony Blair told the opening ceremony
this was the first time countries from all over Europe had been
brought together and, "This is a remarkable moment for Europe."
</P>
<P>
"The whole objective of the conference is to create a stable,
secure and prosperous Europe," Blair said.
</P>
<P>
Blair, whose country holds the present EU presidency, said EU
enlargement, the Kosovo crisis, organized crime, environment
protection and other issues of common concern were expected to be
discussed at the one-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook told reporters: "This
(conference) does represent one of the important milestones toward
a new Europe, a European Union which will be stronger and a Europe
that will be united."
</P>
<P>
As a result of EU enlargement, Europe would finally put behind
the division which had scarred the continent for the latter half
of this century, Cook said.
</P>
<P>
Attending the conference are heads of state and government from
the 15 EU members as well as from Bulgaria, the Czech Republic,
Estonia, Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, Poland, Romania, Slovenia,
Slovakia and Cyprus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
