<HEADLINE> Wei Jianxing Stresses Fight against Corruption and Extravagance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, a high-ranking
Chinese official, today called for making persevering efforts to
combat corruption in a group discussion attended by deputies from
Heilongjiang province to the National People's Congress (NPC), in
session here since last week.
</P>
<P>
The Communist Party of China (CPC) and the Chinese government
have put great emphasis on improving the Party's work style,
building a clean government and fighting corruption, said Wei, who
is a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of
the CPC Central Committee and secretary of the CPC Central
Commission for Discipline Inspection.
</P>
<P>
Despite successes in the fight against corruption, he said,
corruption is still a severe problem in the country.
</P>
<P>
"Some forms of corruption have kept spreading," he said.
"People are not happy about the situation and hope that our Party
would take more resolute measures to achieve greater successes in
eradicating corruption."
</P>
<P>
Besides the need to continue the anti-corruption campaign, Wei
stressed the importance of leading an ethical way of life and
having a fine style of work.
</P>
<P>
"Party and government departments should promote a change of
social mood and ethics by having a correct lifestyle and a fine
style of work," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wei said that, while corrupted officials are after all few in
number, problems concerning lifestyle and style of work are
widespread.
</P>
<P>
"A few leading cadres are given to a life of comfort and
extravagance," he said. "They are corrupting our Party."
</P>
<P>
"Efforts at putting an end to extravagance must not be regarded
as 'much ado about nothing'," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wei called for an earnest implementation of an eight-point
Party and government decree that aims to put to a stop
extravagance and waste, including stipulations on the use of cell
phones by officials and a ban on gift giving at meetings.
</P>
<P>
Wei also called for concentrating resources on investigating
serious corruption cases and bringing to justice corrupted
officials.
</P>
<P>
"We should never allow corrupted elements to have a place to
hide within the Party, as Jiang Zemin has pointed out," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the importance of doing away with the root
causes of corruption and enhancing supervision over people with
power. 
</P>
</TEXT>
