<HEADLINE> Dalian Selected as Candidate for Exemplary City Honor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN March 12 (Xinhua) -- Dalian, a coastal city in northeast
China, has emerged as a top candidate for selection as an
exemplary city in the field of environmental protection, announced
Wang Yangzhu, deputy director of the National Environmental
Protection Agency (NEPA).
</P>
<P>
Wang, chairman of the Chinese Experts Committee for Exemplary
Cities of Sino-Japanese Environmental Cooperation, said his
committee inspected and selected Dalian as a top candidate.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Premier and Japanese Prime Minister reached an
agreement at the end of last year to select 2-3 exemplary cities
involved in Sino-Japanese environmental cooperation. The agreement
also calls for Japan to provide financial assistance to establish
pollution treatment projects in selected cities.
</P>
<P>
Both countries have formed experts committees, and the first
Sino-Japanese Experts Committee Meeting to select exemplary cites
is slated for late March.
</P>
<P>
"The list of candidates includes Guiyang, Chongqing and
Dalian," according to Wang.
</P>
<P>
Seven pollution treatment projects in Dalian were granted
priority as part of the Sino-Japanese Environmental Cooperation
Program. Said project involve air and dust pollution treatment, as
well as the relocation of polluting enterprises. 
</P>
