<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Learning Chinese Turning Trendy in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 12 (Xinhua) -- From official language training
seminars to private Putonghua (standard spoken Chinese) agencies,
learning Putonghua is in high fashion in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of Macao civil servants, students, clerks and
businessmen have joined the army of Putonghua learners, either for
better jobs, better business opportunities or a better future
after 1999 when Macao's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Behind the fashion is also the encouragement of the Macao
government and actual demand in their daily life, observers here
say.
</P>
<P>
Putonghua course was first launched in the late 1970s mainly to
train interpreters. It did not gain much momentum until China and
Portugal signed the Joint Declaration on the question of Macao in
1987.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, more and more people, especially civil
servants, have started learning Putonghua in their spare time.
</P>
<P>
The training course at the Macao Institute of Engineering
(MIE), the largest official language training center in Macao,
trained more than 2,000 Putonghua learners last year, and the
number is expected to approach 3,000 this year.
</P>
<P>
The language promotion center under the Department of Education
and Youth, the University of Macao and some other non-governmental
organizations are also running Putonghua training courses.
Putonghua course is compulsory in many local middle schools.
</P>
<P>
Observers say the fact that civil servants make up the
remarkable proportion among Putonghua learners is closely
connected to the approaching of the handover.
</P>
<P>
"Chinese language is increasingly widely used with the
implementation of the policy of 'using Chinese as an official
language,'" said Lei Heong Iok, vice-president of the MIE, in an
interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"If the civil servants do not command good Chinese, they will
have difficulties in their work and daily life in the future. Many
of them have now realized that," he said.
</P>
<P>
He told Xinhua that government officials at different levels
have been to his institute to study Chinese. Among the top names
are the president of the Macao Legislative Assembly, a
vice-president of the Leal Senado (Municipal Council) and the
director of the Macao Posts and Telecommunications Department.
Many, including Macao-born Portuguese civil servants, also sent
their children to the training seminar to learn Chinese.
</P>
<P>
The efforts of the Macao government and the support from
China's inland areas are important factors to fuel the fashion,
observers noted.
</P>
<P>
Following the signing of the Joint Declaration, the Macao
government promptly announced policies to encourage the promotion
of both Portuguese and Chinese in Macao. Universities and other
related language bodies in China's inland areas gave great support
to the promotion of Chinese language in Macao as well.
</P>
<P>
For most ordinary citizens, they learn Putonghua because they
need it. Exchanges in cultural, political and economic fields with
 China's inland areas have increased, and Putonghua-speaking
visitors to Macao more than doubled in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
"It is now a must for many businessmen and clerks to be able to
 speak Putonghua now," an analyst said, adding that "To them,
speaking Putonghua means better business and better job
opportunities."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
