<HEADLINE> Service Sector Provides Jobs for Nanning's Laid-off Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The service industry in south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region has absorbed nearly 60
percent of the region's laid-off workers, according to local
officials.
</P>
<P>
Some 155,900 laid-off workers found new jobs last year,
according to local statistics. About 94,500, or 59.3 percent of
those people, found jobs in the service sector.
</P>
<P>
In recent years local authorities moved to adjust the economic
structure. Transportation, telecommunications, financial services,
commercial centers, hotels and tourism were greatly boosted.
</P>
<P>
Nanning, the region's capital, now has 21,800 job-seekers, said
Mayor Lin Guoqiang.
</P>
<P>
The thriving service sector gives the region more opportunities
for helping laid-off workers, Lin said. 
</P>
