Tibet Autonomous Region continued the nationwide campaign against
fake and substandard products today by destroying 550,000 yuan
worth of goods in the suburbs of Lhasa.
</P>
<P>
Similar activities were being carried out simultaneously in
seven other cities and prefectures in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, more than 2,500 instances of bogus
goods were discovered and 40 illicit workshops closed down, and 10
million yuan worth of goods confiscated.
</P>
<P>
Industrial and commercial officials have helped consumers
recover as much as four million yuan in losses, according to
officials. 
