cents while Commonwealth fell 18, ANZ was three cents weaker and
Westpac improved 1.4 cents.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index closed 6.8 points down at 1157.6.
</P>
<P>
BHP drifted 19 cents lower and WMC dropped 5.6.
</P>
<P>
The gold index fell 5.6 points to 1103.2 as the bullion price
fell 1.25 per ounce to 294.35 US dollars per ounce.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 382.89 million shares at a value of 1.033
billion Australian dollars (686.9 million US dollars), with falls
outnumbering rises 592 to 523. 
