<HEADLINE> Int'l Maritime Conference to Focus on Trans-Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The fourth biennial
International Maritime Conference will be held in Malaysia in June
to focus mainly on trans-border trade development and
facilitation, an organizer said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Other issues include the globalization of trade and services
and its implications to ports, shipping and related agencies and
risk cover management during turbulent times as well as the recent
changes to the Malaysian merchant shipping law, Malaysian Maritime
Institute President Capt. Mohd Azmi Ahmad told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the conference is "Maritime Industry: Meeting New
and Changing Demand Conditions in Asia".
</P>
<P>
Mohd Azmi said, "We are of the view that the conference is
timely as it is important for the practitioners in the maritime
industry as well policy makers to keep abreast with the major
trends developing in the industry."
</P>
<P>
Some 120 people from Argentina, Britain, Holland, Hong Kong,
Indonesia, Thailand and the United States would attend the
conference to be held here on June 9 and 10.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the World Bank, Malaysian Institute of Economic
Research, International Ship Managers Association of the United
Kingdom, Australian Maritime College, Port of New York/New Jersey
are expected to speak at the conference. 
</P>
