<HEADLINE> Resettlement Project Benefits Kazak Herdsmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The fact that Beshan, a Kazak
herdsman living in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, had
never seen a 50-yuan note prior to 1994, had little influence on
his family's 1997 earnings of 30,000 yuan and total assets of
200,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The family of nine is one of more than 4,000 Xinjiang families
which have participated in the region's resettlement project.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the project is to move more than 50,000 households
out of remote mountainous areas. Hami Prefecture in eastern
Xinjiang has assumed the lead in related efforts.
</P>
<P>
The prefecture has relocated 1,600 families of herdsmen, with
their annual per capita having since jumped to over 1,000
yuan. The prefecture also organized resettled farmers to explain
their successful experiences.
</P>
<P>
The successful efforts have convinced an increasing number of
herdsmen to follow suit. For example, Hami planned to relocate 600
households in 1997, but actually moved more than 800 families by
the end of the year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
