<HEADLINE> East China City Greener Now </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, March 12 (Xinhua) -- People who visit Ningbo, a coastal
city in east China's Zhejiang Province, are surprised to see the
large area of lawns emerging in this port city with many highrise
buildings and well-lighted streets.
</P>
<P>
Local officials have attributed the additional landscaping to
recent government efforts.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the city has more than 2,000 hectares of grass,
including 120 hectares planted in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Forest belts have been planted along the city's nine major
thoroughfares and six rivers. Trees also have been planted on more
than 60 residential blocks.
</P>
<P>
This year, the city government plans to expand the landscaping
program by 50 hectares, which will increase the city's per capita
lawn coverage by 0.8 square meters. Last year, the city's per
capita lawn coverage rose by 0.6 square meters. The city will also
invest 50 million yuan to plant 6.5 million trees in the next five
years. 
</P>
