<HEADLINE> Macao CPPCC Member on Macao's Return to China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- A Macao member of the Ninth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), the top advisory body, said here today that
people in Macao are confident in the region's smooth return to
the motherland at the end of next year.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Macao constitutes another great event for the
Chinese nation," said Member Ho Teng Iat, a noted entrepreneur in
Macao, at a speech meeting of the ongoing First Session of the
Ninth CPPCC National Committee this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Ho said that Macao's return would put a complete end to the
history in which Chinese territory is occupied and ruled by
foreigners, and thoroughly wash off the historical humiliation of
the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Macao is of great historical and realistic
significance to the peaceful reunification of the motherland, as
well as to China's reinvigoration," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that with its 400-year-plus history as a free harbor
and long-practiced policy of a free economy with low taxes, Macao
will still play a major role in promoting trade and economic
exchanges between China and the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
"The tremendous achievements scored by the motherland's
interior areas in economic growth have provided a powerful backing
for Macao's long-term prosperity and stability," he said.
</P>
<P>
With only one year and nine months to go before Macao returns
to China, he said, it is necessary to step up various kinds of
preparatory work.
</P>
<P>
"The Portuguese side should be urged to take quickest possible
actions to settle major problems related to Macao's return, such
as those to localize Macao's civil service, localize laws and
confirm the Chinese as the official language of Macao," he noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
