<HEADLINE> Meeting on How to Improve Skin Quality Held in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Tanners
Association (ETA) and Pittards Plc, probably the world's largest
producer of glove leather, held their ninth annual meeting here
recently on how to improve skin quality.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, co-chaired by ETA Chairman Alem Asfaw and
Managing Director of Pittards Plc Rag Hankey, also discussed
ongoing technical advances in the industry and environmental
issues, ''The Ethiopian Herald'' reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Forty participants of the meeting later agreed on the
importance of improving the state of raw skin in order to
increase the country's foreign currency earnings.
</P>
<P>
Many options were proposed and discussed by the participants
to assist the Ethiopian tanning industry in producing better
quality raw materials in future and process it to international
standards.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have agreed to form a joint committee so as to
follow up the implementation of the recommendations reached at
the end of the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia stands first in Africa and tenth in the world in its
livestock resource. Hides and skins export is second largest
export item in the country next to coffee.
</P>
<P>
However, the quality of hides and skins affect the income of
hard currency. For example, Ethiopian tanneries lose nearly seven
million Dollars due to defects caused by sheep skin disease every
year. 
</P>
