<HEADLINE> HK Official Calls Legislative Election Historic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The forthcoming Legislative
Council (LC) election is a historic event for the residents of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), an SAR government
official said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Secretary for Constitutional Affairs Michael Suen said the
election, scheduled for May 25 this year, is of historic
significance as it is the first ever since Hong Kong's handover
and the establishment of the SAR in July last year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a kick-off ceremony here on Thursday of an
exhibition to promote the election, Suen said the LC speaks for
the SAR residents and its work is closely linked with their daily
life. Participating in the voting to elect their representatives
to the council is both the right and obligation of the SAR's
eligible voters, he added.
</P>
<P>
Suen said all information concerning the election will be
provided to residents and voters through various means including
the media, a special publication and direct mailings to voters'
homes.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, to be followed by a series of others throughout
Hong Kong, tells visitors of the functions of the LC, the division
of constituencies, key events and other election-related matters.
</P>
