<HEADLINE> Great Lakes Region Needs Fund for Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- A United Nations report
indicated that the Great Lakes region countries need 55O.5
million U.S. Dollars to resettle their refugees.
</P>
<P>
According to the Monitor newspaper Thursday, a United Nations'
Consolidated Appeal (UNCA) report proposed to use the fund to
carry out humanitarian work especially in areas experiencing
internal conflicts and influx of refugees.
</P>
<P>
The region suffered from ethnic conflict between Hutu and
Tutsi tribes both in Burundi and Rwanda, and internal rebellion
in western and northern Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Last year alone saw some 1.3 million Rwandan refugees being
repatriated from other countries to their homeland. Rebels in
Uganda also forced thousands to leave their home. Besides,
natural disasters such as floods, drought and diseases also
claimed many local people.
</P>
<P>
The proposed fund is to be used in Burundi, Democratic
Republic of Congo, Rwanda, Tanzania and Uganda, the report added.
</P>
</TEXT>
