<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed lower Thursday in thin volume on the
absence of fresh leads.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the Composite Index fell 11.68 points to close at
its lowest level Thursday at 698.23, the Emas Index eased 2.31
points to 177.27, Industrial Index shed 15.61 points to 1,262.36
and the second board index was 0.65 of a point higher at 179.11.
</P>
<P>
Losers thumped gainers by 504 to 178 while 116 were unchanged
and 112 others were untraded.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's turnover fell to 176.178 million shares valued at
416.311 million ringgit (107.853 million U.S. dollars) from
260.045 million shares worth 540.072 million ringgit (139.915
million U.S. dollars) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
