valued at 363.250 million ringgit (94.106 million U.S. dollars)
from Wednesday's 232.572 million shares worth 472.810 million
ringgit (122.490 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The second board's turnover eased to 17.420 million shares
valued at 53.061 million ringgit (13.746 million U.S. dollars)
from 27.473 million shares worth 67.261 million ringgit (17.425
million U.S. dollars) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Off market business eased to 9.235 million shares valued at
29.617 million ringgit (7.673 million U.S. dollars) from 11.961
million shares worth 81.477 million ringgit (21.1 million U.S.
dollars ) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
