<HEADLINE> China Makes Flotation Therapeutic Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese experts have created the
country's first flotation therapeutic equipment, trying to cure
psychological disorders resulting from various daily pressure.
</P>
<P>
The equipment can help reduce anxiety, depression, fear,
dizziness and insomnia, the experts at Beijing Medical University
said here recently.
</P>
<P>
The flotation therapy -- which is prevalent in Canada, Japan,
the United States and many European countries -- also helps cure
patients suffering from hypertension, diabetes or rheumatoid
arthritis, medical experts said.
</P>
<P>
In the treatment, doctors make patients float on the liquid
with various medicine.
</P>
<P>
People release endorphins, hormones with curative aspects, when
floating, according to scientists.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, doctors can reach their goals of psychological
analysis and hypno-analysis using the flotation therapy.
</P>
<P>
Students and athletes can take advantage of the treatment as
well, the experts said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980312.0162 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taiwan Authorities Urged to Cast away Illusion  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang (RCCK) today
appealed to the Taiwan Authorities to respond earnestly and
positively to President Jiang Zemin's eight-point proposal and
take practical measures to hold political negotiations across the
Taiwan Straits at an earlier date.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a meeting of the Ninth National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), Zhou
Tienong, vice-chairman of the RCCK's Central Committee, said the
growth of cross-straits relations and realization of the
motherland' reunification concern the fundamental interests of the
Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
This also represents an inevitable trend of historical
development and the common aspiration of the people across the
Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
How to handling the cross-straits relations well and keep a
correct orientation for Taiwan's future development has become the
key issue that all political parties and political forces in
Taiwan should face squarely, he said.
</P>
<P>
The "One China" principle is a matter which has an bearing on
the state sovereignty and national dignity, and it should be
adhered to unswervingly, he noted. As part of China, the future of
Taiwan hinges on the reunification of the motherland, which is the
common understanding reached by the majority of the Chinese on
both sides of the Taiwan Straits and the international community
as a whole, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, it is regrettable
</P>
<P>
that Taiwan Authorities made many assertions in an attempt to
break away with the framework of one China and fabricate a "basis"
for "splittism and division of rule." Leaders of Taiwan
authorities have gone too far to accept the principle of "One
China", he said.
</P>
<P>
"We hold that the fundamental differences across the Taiwan
Straits hinges on the fact that whether the "One china" principle
is kept to or the scheme of "Two Chinas" or "One China, One
Taiwan" is followed, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
