<DOCNO> XIE19980312.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taiwan Urged to Cast Illusion  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The two opposing political positions are bound to determine the
destiny of the Taiwan people and lead to the entirely different
orientations of development for Taiwan, he added.
</P>
<P>
Neither "Taiwan Inndence" nor "independence of Taiwan" will
have the future, and these schemes will eventually subject Taiwan
to the appendage of foreign forces and throw the Taiwan people in
the abyss of suffering, he said.
</P>
<P>
Only the two sides work hand-in-hand for the reunification of
the motherland, can Taiwan maintain a long-term stability and
prosperity, can the people on both sides enjoy the lasting peace and
the dignity of the motherland, and can the Chinese nation have a
bright future, he said.
</P>
<P>
He expects the people of insightedness within the Kuomintang
give prominence to the national interests and the well-being of
the 21 million Taiwan people, comply with the wishes of Taiwan
people, discard the erroneous stand of "splitt and division of
rule", return to the stance of "One China" and make due
contributions for the direct links of postal, air and shipping
services and trade between the two sides and promote the great
cause of the reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Holding political negotiations across the straits is the key to
the improvement and development of relations between the two
sides. It is both a rational and flexible option to steadily
implement the concept of peaceful reunification through holding
political negotiations, Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, political negotiations between the two sides will
also remove obstacles for the business routine and economic talks
across the straits and help break the political deadlock and
promote healthy development of the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Finally, on behalf of the of RCCK Central Committee, Zhou urged
the Taiwan Authorities to cast away unrealistic illusions, make an
earnest and positive response to the eight-point proposal put
forward by President Jiang Zemin and his reiteration at the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China and take
concrete measures to hold political talks across the straits.
</P>
</TEXT>
