<HEADLINE> Mozambican Exports Increase by 7.5 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique exported 128,000 tons
of various goods last year, worth 234 million U.S. Dollars,
recording a 7.5 percent increase over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Jose Paulo, director of the National
Bureau of Commerce, the national newspaper Noticias reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to Paulo, prawn is the biggest article, accounting
for 38.5 percent of the total amount. It is followed by cotton,
at 9.5 percent of the total export.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique produced 25,000 tons of sugar in 1997, almost all
of which was exported to the United States, earning about 12.82
million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
However, due to its failure in exporting enough electricity to
South Africa, Mozambique's income was deducted by 16 million
Dollars. 
</P>
