<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Continue Falling on Weak Futures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices in Tokyo fell sharply
for the second straight trading day Thursday, led by sliding
futures issues ahead of Friday's special quotation to settle March
options and futures contracts.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei average of 225 selected issues on the First Section on
the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 180.92 points, or 1.08 percent, from
Wednesday's close to 16,575.22.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
issues on the major section, declined 11.40 points, or 0.90
percent, to 1,249.71.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the section decreased to an estimated 360 million shares
from Wednesday's 419.69 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Civil engineering company Toyo Construction was Thursday's volume
leader.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,330 issues listed on the First Section, losers outpaced
gainers 795 to 309 with 158 issues unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
