<HEADLINE> Government Advisors on Rule of Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Several members of the Ninth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), the top advisory body, today underlined the
importance of instituting the practice of a rule by law across the
country.
</P>
<P>
At a speech meeting of the ongoing First Session of the Ninth
CPPCC National Committee here today, the advisors noted that
everything in China, including its political life, economic
growth, social progress and the people's everyday life, should be
administered and managed according to law instead of being
subjected to anyone's personal will.
</P>
<P>
Member Zhang Baowen and Member Huang Jingjun, both senior
leaders of the Central Committee of the China Democratic League,
one of China's eight non-Communist parties, made a joint speech on
rule of law.
</P>
<P>
"In his report to the 15th National Congress of the Communist
Party of China (CPC), Jiang Zemin had proclaimed for the first
time that 'administering the country according to law and building
a socialist nation ruled by law' is a basic strategy for the CPC
in leading the Chinese people in the management of the country,"
they noted.
</P>
<P>
This constitutes a major theoretical breakthrough and a
fundamental change in the way China is being managed, they
acknowledged.
</P>
<P>
In order to promote a rule of law in China nowadays, they
suggested that greater efforts be made to improve the socialist
legal system, establish a clean and efficient law enforcement
system and a fair judicial system, develop a system of democratic
supervision and enhance the legal awareness of all the people.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, member Mei Yangzheng, chairman of the Henan
Provincial Committee of the Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese
Kuomintang, another non-Communist party in China, described a rule
of law as a cornerstone of the country's development.
</P>
<P>
The administering of the country according to law comprises
four major factors, namely, legislation, spread of legal
knowledge, law enforcement and the CPC leadership and supervision
over it, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that improved leadership and supervision are the
basic guarantee for the successful establishment of a rule of law.
</P>
<P>
"Only by strengthening the leadership of the CPC and through
the development of a supervisory system that includes the Party,
people's congresses and the government, can we achieve the maximum
and best efficiency in the promotion of a rule of law," Lu said.
</P>
</TEXT>
