<HEADLINE> Property Market Recovering from Slump in Beihai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Property business in the
beach-side city of Beihai continued to pick up this year following
recovery from slumps in previous years.
</P>
<P>
In January, property transactions in this city in Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region reached 150 million yuan (18.072 million
U.S. dollars), a year-on-year increase of 93.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
One of the first coastal cities opened to overseas investment,
Beihai on the Beibu Gulf was once a focal point for property
developers from across the country. However, the market plummeted
around 1995 due to the state's tightening-the-belt policy.
</P>
<P>
The market picked up again in May of 1996 when the local
government adopted new land policies resulting in huge cuts in
government profits. In 1997, transactions rose by 15 percent over
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to market sources, the conveniently located
residential apartments managed by high-quality property management
companies are selling especially well, while offices and villas
are still lacking demand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
