<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen on HK Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Qian Qichen said at
a press conference here today that he has every confidence in the
up-coming election of the Legislative Council in the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR), which will be conducted in a
fair, just and open manner.
</P>
<P>
In response to questions at the press conference, Qian said the
coming May will see the election for the first legislative council
in Hong Kong. The method for the election has been formulated by
the Hong Kong SAR government, the election will be organized and
run by the SAR government, and all the preparations are underway.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the central government does not have any plan
to send any people there to monitor the election.
</P>
<P>
The deputies to the National People's Congress and members of
the CPPCC National Committee from the HKSAR have come to Beijing,
which demonstrates that the representatives from the HKSAR are
also in the position to participate in the discussions and
administration of the state affairs of the whole of China, he
noted, adding that they have not come to Beijing for the purpose
of discussing affairs concerning the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
Concerning individual remarks, everybody has his freedom for
what he likes to say, Qian said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
