Leonean President Ahmed Tejan Kabbah, who was ousted in a coup
last May, back to capital Freetown from exile and the end of
military rule.
</P>
<P>
Iran regards the return of the popular legitimate government
and civilian rule in Sierra Leone as a victory of justice and a
great success in the country. 
