<HEADLINE> CPPCC Vice-Chairman Meets With Japanese Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Wang Zhaoguo, vice-chairman of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
National Committee, met with Ryojiro Kojima, chairman of the Board
of Kojima Press Industry Corporation LTD of Japan, and his party
here today.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that the Chinese and Japanese peoples enjoy a long
history of friendship. But the aggressive wars against China
launched by the Japanese militarism in the modern history had
brought about catastrophe to both the Chinese and the Japanese, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
He said: "We should understand this past experience properly to
avoid the repeat of the history and maintain the Sino-Japanese
friendship from generation to generation."
</P>
<P>
Wang voiced his thanks and appreciation to Kojima's generous
donation to the education sector in northwest China's Qinghai
Province over the past decade. He also expressed his hope that
Kojima would continue to dedicate himself to the growth of the
Sino-Japanese friendship and to the economic and social
development in Qinghai.
</P>
<P>
Kojima said that he was honored to have been conferred the
titles of "Honorary Citizen of Qinghai Province" and
"Ambassador of Sino-Japanese Friendship". He told Wang that he is
willing to expand the cooperation between his firm and Qinghai
Province.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese visitors are here on a visit to China as guest of
the Qinghai provincial government. 
