<HEADLINE> Foreign Investors Enjoying Convenient Service in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 12 (Xinhua) -- If a foreign investor has a
project in mind in Guangzhou, he gets invited to the second floor
of the new wing of the Dongfang Hotel.
</P>
<P>
There he can find 63 "windows" offering all the services he
needs to start his business: foreign trade, taxation, banking,
accounting, legal affairs and public security to mention only a
few.
</P>
<P>
Because of the convenient and expeditious services it offers to
foreign investors, the "General Office for Foreign Economic
Relations and Trade," founded in 1985, has become a national model
of the foreign economic relations and trade departments.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 alone the "office" received more than 80,000 overseas
investors, handled more than 60,000 investment and business cases,
dealt with more than 30 complaints and collected 250 million yuan
(30.12 million U.S. dollars) in fees on an acting basis.
</P>
<P>
The office also serves as a bridge between local companies and
foreign investors by launching conferences and organizing
inspection tours.
</P>
<P>
To avoid occurrence of random charges on overseas-funded
companies, the office was authorized by the Guangzhou municipal
government in 1995 to collect fees with unified standards and an
open account.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
