Capital Airport, which handled 16.9 million passengers last year.
</P>
<P>
Hongqiao International Airport remains the country's leader in
handling air freight.
</P>
<P>
One of the country's busiest airports, Baiyun in Guangzhou,
capital of south China's Guangdong Province, served 12.51 million
passengers in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The country's civil aviation sectors handled a record 100
million passengers last year, with take-offs and landings
increasing 20.4 percent over 1996 to reach 1.4 million. 
