<HEADLINE> Malaysia Urges Serbs to Defuse Crisis in Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia deplores the recent
outbreak of violence in Kosovo and urges Serb authorities to act
immediately to defuse the crisis, Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad
Badawi said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia has been following the situation closely and is
disappointed that there is no sign of a respite, the minister said
in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"We hope the Serb authorities will take heed of the concerns of
the international community and act immediately to defuse the
crisis," Abdullah said.
</P>
