<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Developing Multi-media Telecommunications Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's economically booming Guangdong Province, expects rapid
development in its multi-media telecommunications network, with
the number of Chinanet users rising from 4,000 to 10,000.
</P>
<P>
The city's network was hooked up with the Internet through
service providers in Beijing and Shanghai. Last year, the city got
its own outlet to the Internet, with 220 of its simulated lines
replaced by 800 digital ones.
</P>
<P>
The network should maintain its growth momentum in 1998, with
another 1,200 digital lines to be installed soon, according to an
official with the city's telecommunications administration. The
official said the network's transmitting speed will be
accelerated, with more convenient services. 
