<HEADLINE> Hangzhou Invests Heavily in Green Belt Reconstruction Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 12 (Xinhua) -- A 70-meter wide green belt will
be planted along the Donghe River in Hangzhou, capital of East
China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
As the largest urban-reconstruction project in the city, the
the recently started project will demolish old buildings and
houses along four kilometers of the river and replace them with
trees and lawns.
</P>
<P>
Donghe River is adjacent to West Lake and linked to the Grand
Canal. Flanking the river are many shabby houses.
</P>
<P>
After a seven-year feasibility study, the government of
Hangzhou decided to invest 2 billion yuan in the reconstruction
project.
</P>
<P>
The project, scheduled for completion in five years, is
expected to add to the city's beautiful scenery.  
