<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Strengthens Quarantine on Poultry Sold to Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province is
tightening its inspection process for fresh and live poultry sold
to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Under new measures, sellers of live poultry must present a
certificate of inspection issued by veterinary quarantine stations
at or above the county level.
</P>
<P>
Only registered processing plants are entitled to process
poultry sold to Hong Kong. Commodity inspection authorities will
offer quarantine examinations on the spot, and issue a
qualification certificate after the examination is completed
satisfactorily.
</P>
<P>
Fresh poultry must be packed separately, with the package
bearing the sanitation mark of the factory. The products must also
be shipped in cold storage containers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
