<HEADLINE> Shanghai Attracts Foreign Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest
commercial center, has attracted tens of thousands of foreign
experts in recent years.
</P>
<P>
A local government official said that an average of 20,000
foreign experts have kept coming each year to work in the
economic, technological, cultural, publications, education, health
care, media and sports sectors of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The experts are from a dozen of developed countries such as the
United States, Britain, France and Japan, as well as some developing
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
