<HEADLINE> 2,000 Congolese (K) Refugees to Go Home Every </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania will launch a new
operation to repatriate refugees from the Democratic Republic of
Congo, The Guardian paper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to a latest decision by the Commission for the
Repatriation of Congolese Refugees in Tanzania, 2,000 Congolese
refugees will be repatriated every week starting from the end of
the month, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
