countries and officials with the United Nations High Commission
for Refugees (UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
Since the repatriation exercise started last September, more
than 24,000 Congolese refugees have voluntarily gone back to
their country, despite difficulties of floods caused by El Nino
rains, said the Ministry of Home Affairs. 
