<HEADLINE> Park Established to Help Protect 500-Year-Old Walnut Tree </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, March 12 (Xinhua) -- A 500-year-old walnut tree is
being well-protected by the villagers and local government at
Bagqi Town of Hotan County, Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous region, who
established a seven-hectare plot for a park around it.
</P>
<P>
Known as the king of walnut trees, it is 10 meters high with a
trunk diameter of three meters. The width of its crown is 30
meters.
</P>
<P>
The tree is growing vigorously despite some damage to its
trunk. Every year it bears 2,500-to-3,000 walnuts.
</P>
<P>
As early as 1972, an investigation group of the Chinese
Ministry of Forestry and the Forestry Department in Xinjiang
determined that the tree was at least 500 years old.
</P>
<P>
The newly established park around the tree has become a walnut
garden with various fine varieties of walnuts including Xinfeng,
Xinlu and Hochun.
</P>
<P>
Special workers care for the king of walnut trees, such as
watering, providing fertilizer and keeping a record of its growing.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the tree is expected to bear more than 3,000
walnuts this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
