<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Host Int'l Conference on Social Challenges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 12 (Xinhua) -- An International Conference
on Social Challenges of Rapid Economic Transformation will be held
in Malaysia on Saturday, according to an official statement.
</P>
<P>
The conference to be held in Johor Baharu, southern Malaysia,
is being jointly organized by the Institute Sultan Iskandar (ISI)
of Universiti Teknologi Malaysia (Malaysia Technology University)
and Switzerland-based Swiss Academy of Development (SAD).
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that such an international conference is
held in Malaysia and in conjunction with the SAD board meeting and
research meeting.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the Information Department said the research
meeting is to discuss the findings of a joint research carried out
all over the world by the SAD board members on Anomie which is a
sociological term describing a state of chaos due to the rapid
social changes and social disintegration.
</P>
<P>
SAD board members are carrying the research in China, Bulgaria,
South Africa, Western Africa, Germany, Australia and Malaysia, and
similar studies on a comparative basis will soon be conducted in
Singapore, Indonesia, Thailand, Vietnam, Cambodia and the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission's representative from Brussels and the
President of the Swiss Institute of Development will attend the
conference, the statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
