<HEADLINE> China Calls for International Cooperation in Drug Struggle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, March 11 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking Chinese diplomat
called on the international community Wednesday to strengthen
cooperation in a worldwide struggle against drug abuse.
</P>
<P>
"Although some achievements were made last year in the
anti-drug struggle, the world community is still plagued by drug
abuse," said Ambassador Zhang Yishan, head of the Chinese
delegation to the 41st session of the U.N. Commission on Narcotic
Drugs.
</P>
<P>
"The drug issue threatens every country's social stability and
economic development," said Zhang, who is also the Chinese
permanent representative to the U.N. office in Vienna and other
international organizations.
</P>
<P>
"The most efficient way to combat drug abuse is for countries
to pursue a coordinated position on the issue and to strengthen
bilateral and multilateral cooperation," said Ambassador Zhang.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that U.N. drug control authorities
could work out strategies and measures through structural reform
and adjustment in the global anti-drug war.
</P>
<P>
The 41st session of the U.N. Commission on Narcotic Drugs,
which began on Wednesday, will last three days. During the
session, member states will review an annual report from U.N. drug
control authorities. 
</P>
