<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Rejects "Interference" in Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslavian government has
rejected international pressure over its handling of the Kosovo
conflict, describing it as "interference" in its internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
A government statement issued Wednesday said tough action
against terrorism was the legitimate right and duty of a sovereign
state.
</P>
<P>
The government was responding to the emergency meeting on
Monday of the Contact Group on Former Yugoslavia which proposed
sanctions against Belgrade over the conflict between Serbian
police and ethnic Albanians over the past two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The statement described the meeting as a gross violation of
international law against the discussion of a domestic issue of a
sovereign state at international occasions.
</P>
<P>
It reiterated the Yugoslavian government would cooperate with
the international community under conditions of respect to its
sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
The statement called on the international community to refrain
from any action which may encourage the secessionists in Kosovo
and further destablize the province. 
</P>
