area, but also give three seminars on China's transport facilities
and management.
</P>
<P>
The Leipzig Transport and Logistics Fair is one of the few
trade fairs in Germany and Europe which have a complex selection
of goods involving public and cargo transport and includes all
transport companies and their interfaces.
</P>
<P>
The fair will be an excellent opportunity for Chinese
professionals in the transportation industry to get in touch with
their European counterparts, noted the Beijing-based paper.
</P>
<P>
Though China's transport has developed a lot in the past four
decades, it still cannot meet the demands of the rapid economic
development.  
