<HEADLINE> Bell and Beijing University Set up Software Lab </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Bell Laboratories, the
world-renowned research and development arm of the American-based
Lucent Technologies, has signed an agreement with Beijing
University to establish a software technologies laboratory.
</P>
<P>
This joint lab agreement is an extension of the Memorandum of
Understanding signed between Bell Labs and China's State Education
Commission in March 1997, said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The agreement further demonstrated Lucent's dedication to "work
with China, in China and for China", a high ranking official from
the Bell Labs was quoted as saying so.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Beijing University will provide
development staff and Bell Labs will provide software, hardware
and materials as well as staff support.
</P>
<P>
The first joint project between the two will be Lucent's
Inferno Network Operating System and Software Development
Environment. Inferno is a distributed network operating system
that powers information appliances and network elements.
</P>
<P>
Through Inferno, the joint lab plans to build China's first
e-mail and browser interfaces for Internet screen phones and other
embedded devices.  
</P>
</TEXT>
