<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen on Peaceful Progress in Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Chineses Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen said at a press conference here today that it
is beyond any doubt China is prepared to play certain roles in
promoting peaceful process in the Middle East, but China is not a
party to be directly involved in the Middle East question, or a
direct party to help solve the Palestine-Israeli dispute.
</P>
<P>
He said that he has been visiting the middle east area, and he
has been to Egypt, Israel, Syria, and Palestine. He added that he
went there only for the purpose of acquainting himself with the
situation therm and giving Chins's views on the middle east
question.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that China will be a mediator or go-between
on the middle east question, but he considered it a good
opportunity to resolve the middle east dispute and push forward
the middle east peaceful process after the Iraqi Weapon Inspection
Crisis is initially settled.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that all sides concerned to contribute their
efforts, the Chinese vice-premier said.  
