<HEADLINE> Foreign Minister on Financial Crisis in Southeast Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- China is taking a responsible
approach in the recent financial crisis in southeast Asia and
will, as always, develop friendly cooperative ties with these
countries, Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen
said here today.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remarks here this morning at a press conference
sponsored by the ongoing first session of the Ninth National
People's Congress, when asked to comment on the financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
China sympathizes with southeast Asian countries on the impact
of the financial crisis on these countries.
</P>
<P>
He said, "We have also participated in an IMF rescue package
for these countries. China has transferred some amount of money to
the operational budget of the IMF and also provided financial
support for some countries in this region through bilateral
channels."
</P>
<P>
"What is more important, we have not devaluated the Chinese
yuan because of the devaluation of other currencies in this
region. This is a responsible approach that China has taken so
that the financial situation in this region can stabilize at an
early date and turn for the better," he said.
</P>
<P>
"This is a contribution China makes to the region," Qian said.
</P>
<P>
"We are, as always, very positive in developing friendly
relations and cooperation with the southeast Asian countries.
There is no change of policy whatsoever in this regard," he added.
</P>
