<HEADLINE> Indonesia's New Cabinet May Be Announced Saturday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian President Soeharto is
expected to announce the line-up of the 1998-2003 cabinet on
Saturday morning, a source close to the palace said.
</P>
<P>
The source said the hasty formation of the cabinet reflected
the president's deep concern over the lingering economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
"With the formation of the new cabinet, the president can start
working to deal with the economic crisis," said the source, who
requested anonymity, at the sideline of the General Session of the
People's Consultative Assembly (MPR) here Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Other sources also confirmed that preparations have been made
for the scheduled 9:00 a.m. announcement, which will be broadcast
live by the state-owned television station and the five private
television stations.
</P>
<P>
The MPR, which ended its 11-day General Session Wednesday,
elected incumbent President Soeharto to his seventh term of office
on Tuesday and State Minister of Research and Technology B.J.
Habibie as the country's seventh vice president Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Although refusing to divulge names, ruling Golkar Party's
officials said they had prepared a list of eligible candidates to
be presented to the president in case he requests the group's
input.
</P>
<P>
Some political analysts have also stressed that the next
cabinet must be streamlined and be geared to deal with the
economic crisis, the English newspaper "the Jakarta Post" said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Since July last year, Indonesia has been facing with spiraling
inflation, growing unemployment and other serious economic and
financial problems caused by the rapid decline of the rupiah
currency.
</P>
<P>
At present, the rupiah is trading at 10,000 against the U.S.
dollar, compared to 2,400 per dollar early July last year.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's cabinet ministers, like the president and vice
president, will serves a five-year term in office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
