<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU, Macedonia Favor Political Solution to Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) and
Macedonia agreed Wednesday that the Kosovo issue must be settled
politically through negotiations between Belgrade and ethnic
Albanians.
</P>
<P>
EU special envoy Tony Lloyd, who paid a brief visit to Skoplje
Wednesday, and Macedonian Foreign Minister Blagoj Handziski also
agreed that a solution to the Kosovo issue should be found without
altering the borders of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Skoplje, Lloyd, who is also the British
minister of state for foreign and commonwealth affairs, held talks
with Handziski and Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov. He briefed
them on the results of the meeting of the Contact Group on Bosnia
held in London on Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the one-day emergency meeting in London, the Contact Group
reportedly called for "an arms embargo against" Yugoslavia and
threatened to freeze its assets unless Belgrade "halts the
violence in Kosovo and starts talking peace."
</P>
<P>
President Gligorov told Lloyd that Macedonia appreciated the
serious concern of the international community for a peaceful
solution to the Kosovo issue.
</P>
<P>
He said in view of the current situation in Kosovo, the United
Nations Preventive Deployment Forces (UNPREDF) in Macedonia are
very important for the stability of the country.
</P>
<P>
He thanked the Contact Group for proposing an extension of the
UNPREDF mandate in Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Lloyd said that sanctions against Yugoslavia will be tightened
if there is no improvement in the situation in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Lloyd flew to Skoplje from Albania and will continue on to
Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
Kosovo is a province of the Republic of Serbia in
Yugoslavia. Ethnic conflicts in the province, where ethnic
Albanians make up 90 percent of the population, have led to heavy
casualties in the past two weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980312.0327 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
