<HEADLINE> IMF Report Positive About Italian Economic Outlook </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The Italian economy has been given
an encouraging boost in a report for the International Monetary
Fund.
</P>
<P>
The report described government reforms of the civil service
and the retail trade as a sign that the economy will continue to
improve this year.
</P>
<P>
It also recognized that moves to put Italian public finance
back on track would result in a reduction of Italy's debt and
budget deficit.
</P>
<P>
But the IMF remained concerned over the need to push on with
reforms of the tax system already in the pipeline, moves to
deregulate the labor market and further reform of the pension
system. 
