<HEADLINE> Costa Rica Opposes Central American Political Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica's President-elect
Miguel Anel Rodriguez said Wednesday that he opposes a Central
American political union.
</P>
<P>
"There is no real feeling from the Costa Rican people towards
this plan," said Rodriguez during a visit to Honduras.
</P>
<P>
"Our concern is to participate in the economic field and that
trade objectives, reciprocal investments and service movements are
furthered in the future," he said.
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez explained that he opposed political union while
establishing a strong Central American economy was still a
priority. 
</P>
