<HEADLINE> Agassi Beats Bruguera in Champions Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 11 (Xinhua) -- American Andre Agassi beat
14th-seeded Spaniard Sergi Bruguera to reach the third round of
the 2.45 million-dollar Champions Cup tennis tournament in Indian
Wells on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Agassi, playing Bruguera for the first time since he beat the
Spaniard in the 1996 Olympic final, claimed his 12th straight
match win with the 6-1, 7-5 victory.
</P>
<P>
In the third round he will face third-seeded Australian Pat
Rafter, who defeated Agassi en route to the US Open crown last
year.
</P>
<P>
Seventh seed Chilean Marcelo Rios, runner up to Petr Korda of
Australia in Australia open, advanced with a 6-4, 7-6 (7-4)
victory over German qualifier Hendrik Dreekman.
</P>
<P>
Two-time defending champion Michael Chang of the United States
withdrew Tuesday night with a sprained knee. His replacement,
lucky loser Nicolas Lapentti of Ecuador, reached the third round
with a 1-6, 6-3, 6-0 victory over Wayne Black of Zimbabwe.
</P>
</TEXT>
