<DOCNO> XIE19980312.0333 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin's Overseas Investment Focus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Overseas investment in the Chinese
city of Tianjin will be used to transform local traditional
industries, single-story housing, and agricultural developments in
the future.
</P>
<P>
Sixty percent of large state-owned enterprises have been
provided with overseas funds and technology and the other 40
percent are expected to be improved this way by the turn of the
century.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin had spent 2.85 billion US dollars worth of overseas
funds improving 11 million sq.m. of aging houses and moved 500,000
people into now houses by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
To increase the use of overseas investment in agriculture, the
city will build 12 agricultural hi-tech development zones, develop
6 farm products for export, and build an import center for
agricultural technology and equipment.
</P>
<P>
Since last year, the city has approved 100 overseas-funded
agricultural projects, involving 7.64 million US dollars, and
set up processing and export centers for farm and sideline
products, which can earn 100 million US dollars in foreign
exchange a year.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin now has more than 11,000 overseas-funded enterprises
and is one of the leading cities in northern China in terms of use
of overseas investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
