<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France to Build Observatory in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The French Astronomy
Association (AFA) will build a planetarium and observatory in
Panama City, bringing modern astronomical technology to the
Central American country.
</P>
<P>
The AFA Secretary-General Chrisitan Bourdeille and the First
Magistrate of Panama City Mayin Correa on Wednesday signed an
agreement on the project.
</P>
<P>
The observatory will be constructed either in the Municipal
Park or the Summit Botanic Garden due to the absence of trees in
the surrounding area and the clear sky. The French association has
not yet worked out the cost of the project.
</P>
<P>
Besides French scientists, astronomers from Panama and other
countries will be involved in the project, a Panama City official
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
