<HEADLINE> Lazio Reaches Italy Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Czech midfielder Pavel Nedved scored
two goals in three minutes to get Lazio 2-2 draw against Juventus
and a berth in the Italian Cup finals on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
With the draw, Lazio qualified for the finals on a 3-2
aggregate score.
</P>
<P>
In the Italian Cup finals, slated for April 8-19, Lazio will
take on the winner of the other semi-final round between Parma and
AC Milan.
</P>
<P>
Uruguayan Daniel Fonseca put Juventus in lead with a close
range shot in the 35th minute.
</P>
<P>
Nedved hit the equalizer in the 63rd minute and he made it 2-1
three minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Juventus equalizer, in injury time, was an own goal by Lazio's
defender Giuseppe Favalli. 
</P>
