<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Interests Rates Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Interest rates on Italian treasury
bonds and certificates dropped sharply again Wednesday in an
auction of short-term government securities.
</P>
<P>
Ctz treasury zero-coupon certificates at 18 months dropped
from 4.18 percent to 3.91 percent and the 24-month variety slipped
from 4.09 percent to 3.88 percent.
</P>
<P>
The still popular one-year Bot treasury bonds also dropped
sharply, by 0.43 base points, to an all-time low of 4.1 percent
and are expected to fall below the 4 percent threshold in the near
future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
