<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China Province Has 784 Km of Expressways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 12 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province has the longest amount of expressways in the country,
with a total of 784.5 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Construction is underway on 420 km of expressways linking
Dianbai with Zhanjiang and Huadu with Qingyuan.
</P>
<P>
By the turn of the century, the province is expected to have
more than 1,000 km of expressways.
</P>
<P>
This year, it will begin building 250 kilometers of expressways.
One of them is the Guangdong section of the Beijing-Zhuhai
expressway, which will use World Bank loans.
</P>
<P>
To improve local transport, the province will raise money in
different ways, like using loans from overseas, transfering
highway management rights, and the build-operate-transfer (BOT)
method.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
