<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Latin America Agrees to Unify Customs Regulations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, March 11 (Xinhua) -- The 11-nation Latin American
Association for Integration have agreed to unify customs
regulations on valuation, nomenclature and goods of transportation.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made by the customs directors of the member
states -- Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil, Colombia, Chile, Ecuador,
Mexico, Paraguay, Peru, Uruguay and Venezuala -- at a meeting in
Montevideo.
</P>
<P>
They said that a basic common nomenclature will provide
comparisons in customs duties in Latin American nations and
reliable statistics for future negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The eight directors also agreed to unify the regulations on
goods transportation in 60 days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
