<DOCNO> XIE19980312.0344 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Alsgaard Snatches Men's Cross Country Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Thomas Alsgaard of Norway won a
10-kilometer cross country ski race in Falun, Sweden Wednesday and
clinched the men's World Cup overall title for the first time.
</P>
<P>
Alsgaard covered the race in 24 minutes, 20 seconds. Austrian
Mikhail Botvinov finished second, 6.8 seconds behind. Rising
Swedish star Per Elofsson came third in 24.32.7.
</P>
<P>
Alsgaard leads fellow Norwegian Bjorn Dahlie 790 points to 618
in the overall standings.
</P>
<P>
Larissa Lazutina of Russia won the women's overall title by
winning the 5km freestyle in 13.09.7. Italian Stefania Belmondo
was second in 13.15.3. Lazutina leads Norway's Bente Martinsen
673 points to 586 in the overall standings. Belmondo is third with
534 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
