<DOCNO> XIE19980312.0345 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen: China Has Played Unique Role on Iraqi Weapons Issue (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua)-- China has played a due, unique and
positive in a peaceful settlement of the UN weapons inspection
crisis in Iraq, Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian
Qichen said today.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remark this morning at a press conference
sponsored by the ongoing First Session of the Ninth National
People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question about China's role in pursuing a
peaceful solution to the recent Iraqi weapons inspection crisis,
Qian said: "China has not served as a mediator nor has it put
forward any scheme."
</P>
<P>
"It has followed two principles: one is that relevant UN
Security Council resolutions on the issue must be earnestly and
comprehensively implemented; the other is that China is not in
favor of the use of force," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
