<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uruguayan Industry Grows 5.6 percent in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, March 11 (Xinhua)- The Manufacturing industry of
Uruguay grew 5.6 percent last year against 1996, the
National Institute of Statistics reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The metallic, machinery and equipment were the most
dynamic parts with an expansion of 25.3 percent in 1997, which
registered only a small increase in 1995 and 1996.
</P>
<P>
Non-metallic mineral production held second place with 13.2
percent increase.
</P>
<P>
Paper and printing went up to 9.8 percent and metals
rose 9.1 percent. Food, beverage and tobacco sectors grew 7.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
The less dynamical sectors were textiles with a 2.3 increase
and chemicals with 2 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
