<HEADLINE> Slovenia's Peterka Wins Ski Jumping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Slovenia's Primoz Peterka
totalled 262.3 points to win the world cup Ski jumping in Falun,
Sweden on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Peterka recorded a first jump of 120.5 meters and had 128
meters on his second.
</P>
<P>
Austria's Andreas Widhoelzl, who has scored four World Cup
successes this season, cleared 121.5 meters twice for second place
with 258.9 points.
</P>
<P>
Hiroya Saitoh of Japan finished third with 105.5 and 125 meters
for 236.2 points. 
</P>
