<HEADLINE> World No.1 Gade Christensen Upset in All-England </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BIRMINGHAM, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Top seed and world number one
Peter Gade Christensen crashed out of the All-England badminton
championships on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
World No. 9 Ong Ewe Hock of Malaysia edged out the tall Dane
15-8, 8-15, 15-9 in the men's singles third round.
</P>
<P>
In the women's event former champion Susi Susanti of Indonesia
also bowed out.
</P>
<P>
Christensen led 5-3 in the decider but Ong levelled at 6-6 and
then raced 10-6. The top seed fought back to 9-10 but the
Malaysian regained the control and clinched victory on his second
match point.
</P>
<P>
In second round action earlier, second seed Sun Jun of China
eliminated Dutchman Dicky Palyama 15-3, 15-5 while Olympic
champion Poul-Erik Hoyer-Larsen nipped Belgian Ruud Kuyten 15-4,
15-7.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ye Zhaoying, Gong Zhichao and Zhang Ning all reached
the women's singles last eight. Zhang upset Susanti 11-5, 2-11,
11-6. 
</P>
