<HEADLINE> Mexico, Chile to Sign New Trade Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Mexican President Ernesto
Zedillo will visit Chile from March 15-17 to sign a new trade
agreement.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican Foreign Affairs Ministry said the new agreement
will provide new and better regulations to replace the previous
agreement signed six years ago. But details of the new deal have
not yet been released.
</P>
<P>
