<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Post, Telecommunications Sector Grows in Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The post and telecommunication
sector has become one of the fastest-growing areas of central China's
Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The sector has been growing at 50 percent a year in the past
five years. It earned 6.35 billion yuan in business in 1997, a 52
percent rise from the 1996 level.
</P>
<P>
Henan spent 4.4 billion yuan in fixed assets in the sector last
year, up 16 percent from 1996, and added 1.15 million lines
to the handling capacity of the local public telephone switching, 8,000
ports to the long-distance telephone switching, and 370,000 customers
to the mobile communications network.
</P>
<P>
It added 1.1 million telephone customers in 1997, of whom,
580,000 were in urban areas, 280,000 in rural areas, and the
remaining 240,000 were mobile phone users. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
