<HEADLINE> Italian Wins Tirreno-Adriatico Cycling Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Italian Gabriele Balducci on
Wednesday took the first leg of the Tirreno-Adriatico cycling race
in Sorrento as the flu-weakened Tour of France champion Jan
Ullrich withdrew from the competition.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich, who stopped pedaling one hour into the race, said he
was confident he would recover his health by the start of
the Milan-to-San Reclassic on March 21.
</P>
<P>
Balducci took the 133-kilometer leg, beating the pack at the
finish line.
</P>
<P>
Balducci, who completed the stage in three hours, 27 minutes 55
seconds, edged Denma's Lars Michaelsen at the finish line. Another
Dane, veteran Rolf Sorensen, placed fourth, behind Italy's Roberto
Petito. 
</P>
</TEXT>
