<HEADLINE> Barcelona Lifts UEFA Supercup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Barcelona Wednesday got a second
UEFA Supercup title after 1993 by holding Champions Cup holder
Borussia Dortmund to a 1-1 second-leg draw in Dortmund.
</P>
<P>
With Barcelona taking a 2-0 first leg lead, the title was all
but decided on aggregrate by the seventh minute when Brazilian
forward Anderson beat two German defenders to score the game's
first goal.
</P>
<P>
The German club made it 1-1 through Joerg Heinrich at the 65th
minute who knocked in a close-range shot.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona won the Supercup in 1993 against another German club,
Werder Bremen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
