<HEADLINE> U.S. Stocks End at New Highs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 11 (Xinhua) -- U.S. stocks ended higher again
Wednesday with the Dow Jones industrial average up 32.63 points to
a record high of 8,675.75, standing firm above the 8,600 level
which it reached Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The market was fueled by investor enthusiasm and an absence of
bad news, analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Technology shares saw their strong rebound with Compaq, IBM,
Intel and Motorola posing gains. The computer shares suffered
heavy losses last week on their earnings warning.
</P>
<P>
Other major market indicators were also up. The Stand &AMP; Poor's
500 stock list grew 4.22 to 1,068.47 and the New York Stock
Exchange composite index rose 2.30 to 557.30. The two indexes
scored the highest finish for the second day.
</P>
<P>
The technology heavy Nastaq composite index gained 8.34 to
1,756.85.
</P>
<P>
On the smaller companies' line, the Russell 2000 rose 2.50 to
467.12 and the American Stock Exchange composite index rose 1.24
to 713.93.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary figures show that NYSE advancing issues led
decliners 7-5 with 1,743 up, 1,221 down and 499 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume amounted to 652.32 million shares against 631.45
million shares Tuesday. 
</P>
