<HEADLINE> European Shares Mixed, London, Paris Hit New Highs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 11 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe
ended mixed Wednesday, with Frankfurt ending slightly down and
London and Paris hitting new record closing highs.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE 100 had earlier touched an intra-day peak of
5,861.9 before closing at 5,829.8, up only 1.3 points or 0.02
percent, yet its third record close of the month, lifted by a
firmer Wall Street and selective buying of leading stocks.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that different influences, such as possible
European rate hikes amid strong economic growth, the forthcoming
budget and sterling strength will be weighing on the market.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, German shares closed little changed, with the
DAX-30 index down 1.67 points or 0.03 percent at 4,832.76, boosted
by a stronger Dow and the continued strength of the dollar, but
were well off their highs as the market consolidated recent record
gains.
</P>
<P>
The CAC-40 index in Paris closed at 3,539.43, up 17.92 points
or 0.51 percent, a new closing high, also supported by a strong
Wall Street and firmer dollar.
</P>
<P>
Traders said that financials were quite strong and dollar based
stocks were doing well. 
</P>
